The paper deals with inapproximability results for hypergraph coloring, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses techniques related to coding theory, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as another likely sub-category. The problem of hypergraph coloring is closely related to graph theory, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves some results related to combinatorial optimization, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
